<title>Got a Logitech Harmony Link? Get Your Free Upgrade by Simply Contacting Them</title>
<link>https://www.reviewgeek.com/748/got-a-logitech-harmony-link-get-your-free-upgrade-by-simply-contacting-them/</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >https://www.reviewgeek.com/748/got-a-logitech-harmony-link-get-your-free-upgrade-by-simply-contacting-them/</guid>
<description>It is all but impossible to buy a TV without getting some kind of bundled software that’s supposed to make your life easier (but mostly just frustrates everyone). If you’d rather enjoy using your TV (and get a longer life out of it), here’s our picks for streaming sticks and set-top boxes.</description>
<pubDate>Fri, 10 Nov 2017 16:32:21 +0000</pubDate>
<dc:creator>Lowell Heddings</dc:creator>
<og:title>Got a Logitech Harmony Link? Get Your Free Upgrade by Simply Contacting Them</og:title>
<og:type>article</og:type>
<og:description>When the news broke that Logitech was bricking their Harmony Link devices after stopping support, customers were rightly angry — and the backlash has now forced them to change course. They are still bricking your device, but now you can get a free Harmony Hub (normally $99) to replace your Link.</og:description>
<og:image>https://www.reviewgeek.com/thumbcache/648/248/11badf9c80ea6144033fddc34a5ca93f/p/uploads/2017/11/3a224bf9-1.jpg</og:image>
<og:url>https://www.reviewgeek.com/748/got-a-logitech-harmony-link-get-your-free-upgrade-by-simply-contacting-them/</og:url>
<dc:language>en-US</dc:language>
<dc:format>text/html</dc:format>
<dc:identifier>https://www.reviewgeek.com/748/got-a-logitech-harmony-link-get-your-free-upgrade-by-simply-contacting-them/</dc:identifier>
