<title>How to Set Up Alexa Routines to Control Multiple Smarthome Devices at Once</title>
<link>https://www.howtogeek.com/332042/how-to-set-up-alexa-routines-to-control-multiple-smarthome-devices-at-once/</link>
<guid isPermaLink="true" >https://www.howtogeek.com/332042/how-to-set-up-alexa-routines-to-control-multiple-smarthome-devices-at-once/</guid>
<description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332063&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8351.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.ynEJgmM2Xj.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;650&quot; height=&quot;300&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;It’s great to control your smart house with your voice, but it’s even better when you can say one command and have multiple things happen at once. Here’s how to set up Routines to use with Alexa and your Echo devices.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Before this, if you wanted to turn on your lights and the space heater, you would have to give Alexa two separate commands. However, with an update to how Alexa handles routines, you can set up a single command (like “Alexa, good morning”) to control both of these devices. Let’s get started.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;div id=&quot;div-thetop1&quot;&gt;&lt;ins class=&quot;adsbygoogle&quot; data-ad-format=&quot;fluid&quot; data-ad-layout=&quot;in-article&quot; data-ad-client=&quot;ca-pub-9173525300015284&quot; data-ad-slot=&quot;2986027408&quot;/&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&amp;#13;
&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Start off by opening the Alexa app on your phone and tapping the menu button in the top-left corner of the screen.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332064&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8349.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.G4rzjnKPg1.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Select “Routines” from the list.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332065&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8350.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.qchfhy2DLl.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Tap on the round, blue plus button to get started making a routine.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332066&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8351-1.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.D7fv0hTk2v.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;On the next screen, tap on “When this happens”. This is what will trigger the routine.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332067&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8352.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.nIUWArtcze.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Next, you can either give Alexa a command to trigger the routine, or have it trigger at a certain time on certain days.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332068&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8353.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.FwTnpxrHlj.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;If you choose “When you say something”, you’ll type in the phrase that you’ll say to trigger the routine. In this case, I’ll just type “good morning”. So to start the routine whenever I want, I’ll just have to say “Alexa, good morning”. Hit “Save” at the bottom once you type in the command you want to use.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332069&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8354.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.h2Oxs-dFb5.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;If you choose “At scheduled time”, you’ll select a time of the day, as well as what days you want the routine to run at that specific time. Hit “Done” at the bottom when you’re finished with this.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332070&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8355.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.QbQVkrL2Nt.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Once you’ve completed this step, tap on “Add action”. This involves choosing what you want to happen when you say your specific command (or at the specified time).&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332071&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8356.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.my13Du68Lh.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;There are four categories to choose from: News, Smart Home, Traffic, and Weather. These are pretty self-explanatory, but for my purposes with this specific routine that I’m making, I’ll be selecting “Smart Home”.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332072&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8357.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.BATo_vTF1n.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;On the next screen, select either “Control device” or “Turn on scene”. If you want to simply turn a device on or off, you’ll select “Control device”, but if there’s a specific Hue lighting scene that you want activated, you’ll choose it from the list after tapping on “Turn on scene”, which is what I’ll be doing.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332073&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8358.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.D-XLyXA52f.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt; &lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332074&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8359.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.ZOT6zuzPuq.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Once you’ve selected the scene, hit “Add” at the bottom.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332075&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8360.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.Bz8VRg2HSf.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Next, tap on “Add action” to add your next device that you want controlled.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332076&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8361.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.yXJZ4wXvpj.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Again, select “Smart Home”.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332077&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8362.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.3IX2QOhC_b.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;For my space heater, I’m just going to want it turned on, so I’ll select “Control device”.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332078&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8363.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.uhWwvgGG0Q.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Scroll down and select the device you want turned on (or off).&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332079&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8364.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.kuEYzXY0ZK.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;By default, the action will turn on the device, but tap on the big circle to change it if you want. Then hit “Next” at the bottom.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332080&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8365.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.CbZ7aEjXIl.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Tap on “Add” at the bottom to confirm.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332081&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8366.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.vk7lE3cXTX.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;Then, hit “Create” at the bottom to finalize the routine and get it up and running.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;alignnone size-full wp-image-332082&quot; data-pagespeed-lazy-src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/11/xIMG_8367.jpg.pagespeed.gp+jp+jw+pj+ws+js+rj+rp+rw+ri+cp+md.ic.u6_0e8wBbL.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; width=&quot;325&quot; height=&quot;578&quot; src=&quot;https://www.howtogeek.com/pagespeed_static/1.JiBnMqyl6S.gif&quot; onload=&quot;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot; onerror=&quot;this.onerror=null;pagespeed.lazyLoadImages.loadIfVisibleAndMaybeBeacon(this);&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
&lt;p&gt;From now on, whenever you say “Alexa, good morning” (or at the scheduled time), she’ll turn on your lights, as well as your space heater. Of course, you can set a schedule for these devices in their own separate apps, but Alexa makes it a bit more convenient.&lt;/p&gt;&amp;#13;
</description>
<pubDate>Wed, 08 Nov 2017 20:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
